items.name: GhostSpace
items.description:
GhostSpace is a model designed to convey a dark and muted style that feels like a memory. This model is experimental with heavy stylistic bias - it is not a general purpose model. Despite this, the model is quite easy to prompt (prompt examples attached on the model images).

Note: The example image seeds will not yield identical results in the automatic1111 webui. I use a custom noise generator that has incompatible seeds.

Recommendations:

  • Configuration scale can affect the sharpness of the image. You can get very interesting images at a wide range of config scales. A scale of 13 can yield sharp edges and bold contrast, whereas a config scale of 5 might lean closer to a watercolor look.

  • (highly recommended) Upscaling is a very important for getting a clean look. If you don't, then the model can tend to generate a heavily compressed "jpeg" look, which is generally undesirable. I personally switch between R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B and ESRGAN 4x at a denoising strength of 0.5, but any upscaler works fine.

  • This model is designed for artistic exploration, so I'd recommend being experimental with your prompting style. Example prompts are provided attached to the example images.

  • If you want to avoid the watercolor look, adding "watercolor winter cloudy" to the negative prompt can help with that

items.name: Tiny Top Collection: Mosquito Bites
items.description:
Part two of a LoRA set dedicated to small breasted women. There are tons of big boob models, but in my quest to depict realistic women I found that the opposite is sorely misssing. Mosquito bites are the smallest of the small, just a small step up from flat chests.

Unfortunately SD tends to generate small breasts that are bigger than in the training pictures. So I included a set of flat chested women in the training images to reduce the average size.

Trigger words are not strictly necesseary but you can use them to change the balance between the flat and the mosquito bite parts of the training set. The generated breast size also strongly depends on the rest of the prompt. Use the trigger words for fine tuning.

tt_mosquito emphasizes the original training set, tt_flat does the opposite. They don't necessarily make the breasts bigger or smaller, but they do influence the shape or help to make the nipples look realistic. Play around with them.

Standard disclaimer: This model was trained on pictures of white women with epiCRealism. Other ethnicities may follow in the future. Prompts for the sample images are as simple as possible to show what the model is capable of doing without a lot of tweaking. If you like it, I'd be happy to see more extravagant creations.

items.name: Sierra_SCI_v1
items.description:
Trained on screenshots of classic Sierra Online PC games from the early 1990s that used the SCI game engine and had 16-color, EGA graphics. Version 1 has King's Quest IV, Space Quest III and Hero's Quest I (Quest for Glory I). More to be added in future versions of this LoRA.

Usage Tip: Choose one of the games for a style and use the corresponding name in the prompts, like "landscape with of a forest with ahuge tree at the center, kq4", or the full names with numbers, like "a space ship on a huge asteroid, space quest 3"

If you're going for the authentic look, use a very low res, like 328x216 or so, then you can open the generated image in PhotoShop and resize to 320x200 and reduce the colors to 16 with Image>Mode>Index Color and use Palette: Local (Adaptive), Colors: 16, Forced: None, and either Dither: None, or Pattern. This gives pretty good results that are true to the originals. From there, you can upscale the image, but

If you like my model, follow me or buy me a coffee, or just post some images you made, here. I love to see what you folks make with my models!

items.name: [ChumpyChoo] INFP (16 Personalities) LoRA
items.description:
This is a custom LoRA model for the character INFP, also known as Mediator from the website 16 Personalities. I trained the model using 24 high-quality images and utilized the AbyssOrangeMix3 model. I manually removed each watermark from each image used in the training, then upscaled the images for the highest possible quality.

For optimal results, I recommend using the Euler a sampler, with the following recommended parameters:

  • CFG scale of 7

  • 20 steps

  • hires upscaler set to Latent (nearest-exact)

  • 20 hires steps

  • Denoising strength of 0.52

For optimal performance, it is recommended that the weight of the LoRA be set within the range of 0.8-1.

To accurately depict an INFP's appearance, I suggest including green hair, green eyes, head wreath, and green dress in the positive prompt.

Please feel free to leave a comment below if you have any requests for LoRA models.

items.name: vodka_portraits photorealism
items.description:
We are continuing with the most open-source Stable Diffusion fine-tuning series. This time we decided to address the issues of the Vodka v3 model using custom LoRAs, and the results look interesting!
Check out the full post here https://followfoxai.substack.com/p/getting-started-with-loras-vodka

LoRA trained on realistic portrait shots on top of Vodka V3.
Adds photorealism to all kinds of generations when used in combination with the Vodka model.

Overall observations so far:

  • The model can generate very high-quality photorealistic images

  • It also introduced many issues; in some generations, fingers are now extra deformed, and we observe some forgetting of subjects they knew before.

  • The model's diversity decreased, generating more similar images within the same prompt.

items.name: ControlNet QR Code
items.description:
QR Code Conditioned ControlNet Models for Stable Diffusion 1.5 and 2.1

Model Description

These ControlNet models have been trained on a large dataset of 150,000 QR code + QR code artwork couples. They provide a solid foundation for generating QR code-based artwork that is aesthetically pleasing, while still maintaining the integral QR code shape.

The Stable Diffusion 2.1 version is marginally more effective, as it was developed to address my specific needs. However, a 1.5 version model was also trained on the same dataset for those who are using the older version.

Performance and Limitations

These models perform quite well in most cases, but please note that they are not 100% accurate. In some instances, the QR code shape might not come through as expected. You can increase the ControlNet weight to emphasize the QR code shape. However, be cautious as this might negatively impact the style of your output.**To optimize for scanning, please generate your QR codes with correction mode 'H' (30%).**

To balance between style and shape, a gentle fine-tuning of the control weight might be required based on the individual input and the desired output, aswell as the correct prompt. Some prompts do not work until you increase the weight by a lot. The process of finding the right balance between these factors is part art and part science. For the best results, it is recommended to generate your artwork at a resolution of 768. This allows for a higher level of detail in the final product, enhancing the quality and effectiveness of the QR code-based artwork.

Installation

The simplest way to use this is to place the .safetensors model and its .yaml config file in the folder where your other controlnet models are installed, which varies per application.

For usage in auto1111 they can be placed in the webui/models/ControlNet folder. They can be loaded using the controlnet webui extension which you can install through the extensions tab in the webui (https://github.com/Mikubill/sd-webui-controlnet). Make sure to enable your controlnet unit and set your input image as the QR code. Set the model to either the SD2.1 or 1.5 version depending on your base stable diffusion model, or it will error. No pre-processor is needed, though you can use the invert pre-processor for a different variation of results. 768 is the preferred resolution for generation since it allows for more detail.

Make sure to look up additional info on how to use controlnet if you get stuck, once you have the webui up and running its really easy to install the controlnet extension aswell.

items.name: Shizuka Mogami/最上静香 | MILLION LIVE!/ミリオンライブ/ミリシタ
items.description:
LoRA model of Shizuka Mogami (最上静香) from media-mix project THE IDOLM@STER MILLION LIVE! (アイドルマスターミリオンライブ！).

The trigger word is shizuka mogami (million live). Considering the Second Hair Style (SHS) card and alternative hair color in Mirishita, this model don't fix Shizuka's features of hair and eyes. You can reproduce the Shizuka's style of game card illustrations by adding following tags:

*Original style of Shizuka:

black hair, long hair, blue eyes, blunt bangs, sidelocks, half updo, hime cut, blunt ends, hair ribbon/hair bow

*Alternative hair style (SHS, ponytail) of Shizuka:

black hair, long hair, blue eyes, blunt bangs, sidelocks, high ponytail

Of course, you can change Shizuka's features of hair and eyes at your own. Try and enjoy it!

(P.S. I think the size of breasts can be easily adjusted by tags e.g. flat chest / tiny tits / small breasts / medium breasts / large breasts / huge breasts / gigantic breasts and thier various weights, so I delete the tag small breasts during captioning, meaning that the small size of breasts has become an inherent feature bound to the character.)

The LoRA weight of samples is 0.8; you can also try other weights. The greater the weight, the closer the character style is to the game card of THE IDOLM@STER MILLION LIVE! THEATER DAYS (ミリシタ) and the new tachie drawn after the release of the game.

Note: I load my LoRA model through the additional network WebUI plugin, so the prompt of sample illustrations don't contain <lora:XXX:X> tag.

I'll appreciate it if you're willing to use this LoRA model and share AI arts to other people. My models and illustrations are free for everyone, and if you like them, please support me at Patreon or 爱发电.

————————————

跨媒体企划《偶像大师 百万现场》的角色最上静香的LoRA模型

训练时使用的基底模型为animefull-latest；模型的触发词为 shizuka mogami (million live)。考虑到游戏的第二发型卡（SHS）和异色发色卡，本模型没有固定静香的头发和眼睛特征，您可以通过添加以下标签来复刻游戏卡面中静香的风格：

*原有卡面的静香:

black hair, long hair, blue eyes, blunt bangs, sidelocks, half updo, hime cut, blunt ends, hair ribbon

当然，你也可以自由改变静香的头发和眼睛特征，敬请享受！

items.name: Furry Ring Gag
items.description:
ring_yiffy21_v1:

A strength of 0.6 or 0.7 seemed to work best. Use ring_gag as trigger, a few other things like drool, saliva, tongue out can affect the results as well. Trained on Yiffymix 21

ring_yiffy3_v1:

Same as previous, but trained on Yiffymix 3

ring_yiffy3_v2:

A Strength of 0.5 or 0.6 seemed to work sell. It can be very sensitive to negative prompt, I usually didn't use a negative because it tended to make the mouth softer and lower detailed. Use ring_gag as trigger, do not use open mouth as that wasn't part of the captions and can make the mouth look odd. Can also add drool, tongue out or try large mouth, but large mouth can produce some odd results. Used a larger image set. Trained on Yiffymix 3.

modelVersions.name: ring_yiffy3_v2
modelVersions.description: I used a larger image set and it seems to be a little more versatile than the first. It is very touchy when it comes to the negative prompt. Using a "universal negative" prompt I tended to get low detail and softer images around the mouth. No negative worked fairly well. Strength from 0.5 to 0.7 worked the best for me. use ring_gag as trigger, I didn't use open mouth or any combination of that so that can lower the detail. Drool and tongue out can work. It does occasionally produce 3 or 4 ears for some reason.

Miscellaneous - detached sleeves, anklet, bracelet

Checked strength range is 0.7-0.9. Continue to experiment with different settings, trying dataset with lower amount of images then usual this time around.

Review and comment with your experiences, I would appreciate whatever feedback you can provide in order to continue improving my technique.

Trained on Anything V4.5 with anime.vae.pt and CLIP Skip 2.

Inpaint guide: if face on full body shots comes out deformed\not detailed enough - it's easily fixed with single inpaint, whole process takes half a minute. Press "Send to inpaint" button under generated image, mask the face area with drawing tool, choose DDIM sampler, set "Inpaint area" to "only masked", and set denoising strength to 0,5. Press generate and you done!

items.description:
lora有水印，所以反向提示词里记得添加“水印”。

这个lora里有面部，所以与其他lora混着使用时，最好使用lora分层插件，

看看lora在不同权重下的表现

当步数在28时，推荐权重0.4～1

本人电脑性能有限，大家可自行测试。

lora训练基础参数

大模型：chilloutmix

vae:vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned

采样方法：DDIM

There is a watermark in the Lora, so remember to add the word "watermark" in the reverse prompt when using it with other Loras. As this Lora contains a face, it is recommended to use a layered Lora plugin when mixing it with other Loras to see how Lora performs at different weights. When the step number is 28, a weight of 0.4 to 1 is recommended. Please note that my computer performance is limited, so you can test it yourself. The basic training parameters for Lora are as follows:

Large model: chilloutmix

VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned

Sampling method: DDIM.

items.name: Julia / ジュリア (THE IDOLM@STER Million Live!)
items.description:
This LoRA was trained on official illustrations from THE iDOLM@STER MILLION LIVE! and THE iDOLM@STER MILLION LIVE! Theater Days.

I recommend using weight values around 0.7, although higher values (~0.9) can also give good results.

By default, my model generates Julia with her common "tomato" hairstyle, but if you want to change it, please try the "punk_hairstyle" tag (like on example image №2). Additionally, the "blue star on face" prompt can help you add Julia's special sign.

This LoRA is my very first one, so if you have any thoughts to share, please feel free to message me on Twitter: @billyjeanp20.
